    {
      "id": "18f4750c-f3ba-8084-9ee6-f02b52727ade",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The paper proposes a density-based algorithm for group formation. The algorithm starts with random assignment to cluster centers and iteratively adjusts centroids. (this seems awfully similar to k-means lol). The authors also argue against the general goal in group formation: maximize intra-group homogeneity and inter-group heterogeneity. ",
